cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.GT 

This paper deals with the problem of cell association in UAV-enabled cellular networks, which is a topic related to network optimization and communication theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also uses optimal transport theory, which is a mathematical tool for solving optimization problems, suggesting that it could also be categorized under cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). Additionally, the paper proposes a framework for minimizing network delay, which could be considered as a control problem, leading to a possible categorization under cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper characterizes the solution space of the optimal cell association problem, which could be related to game theory, leading to a possible categorization under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
